article.headline: California 77, Oregon 60
article.story: EUGENE, Ore. -- Allen Crabbe scored a career-high 26 points with six 3-pointers and California surged past Oregon in the second half to win 77-60 on Sunday. Jorge Gutierrez also scored 18 and Justin Cobbs added 15 points for the Golden Bears (13-4, 3-1 Pac-12), who beat the Ducks (11-5, 2-2) for the eighth straight time. Crabbe, who also had 12 rebounds, keyed a 23-5 run in the second half that put Cal up 55-38 with 8:55 to play. Crabbe scored 11 points during that stretch with three 3-pointers. Crabbe finished 9 for 16 from the floor and 6 for 8 on 3-pointers. His only first-half points came on a 3-pointer that gave the Golden Bears a 20-17 advantage. Cal led 30-27 at the break. Devoe Joseph led Oregon with 14 points, E.J. Singler scored 12 and Olu Ashaolu had 10 points.
